Package: normr
Type: Package
Title: Normalization and difference calling in ChIP-seq data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given="Johannes",family="Helmuth", email="helmuth@molgen.mpg.de",
    role=c("aut", "cre")))
Author: Johannes Helmuth [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Johannes Helmuth <helmuth@molgen.mpg.de>
Description: Robust normalization and difference calling procedures for ChIP-seq
    and alike data. Count vectors can be obtained from experiment bam files in two
    experiments. Counts are jointly modeled as a multinomial sampling trial with a
    user-specified number of components.
License: GPL-2
Depends:
    R (>= 3.0.0)
LinkingTo: Rcpp
SystemRequirements: C++11
Imports:
    methods,
    GenomeInfoDb,
    GenomicRanges,
    IRanges,
    Rcpp (>= 0.11),
    qvalue (>= 2.2),
    Rsamtools,
    bamsignals (>= 1.2.0)
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 0.9),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
Enhances: BiocParallel
biocViews: Bayesian, DifferentialPeakCalling, Classification, DataImport,
    ChIPSeq, RIPSeq, FunctionalGenomics, Genetics, MultipleComparison,
    Normalization, PeakDetection, Preprocessing
VignetteBuilder: knitr
NeedsCompilation: yes
Collate:
    'BamCountConfig.R'
    'NormRFit.R'
    'RcppExports.R'
    'methods.R'
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
URL: https://github.com/your-highness/normR
BugReports: https://github.com/your-highness/normR/issues
